VERTEX.PBD
==========

(Daria Zieminska)

    Finds z coordinate and its error (ZVER,DZVER) for primary vertex using 
Central Detector data. Must be included in every application that requires this
information BEFORE other packages. If primary vertex is not found the event
is skipped. To get ZVER and DZVER do:

    CALL ZVERTE(ZVER,DZVER)
  
    Current version uses VTX hits. For more details examine sources in
D0$ROOT:[TRACKING_UTIL.DZERO]. To make a modified version of VERTEX package
replace routine VERTEX.FOR with your own. Logical names and files needed are: 


    o static parameter files for run number = xxxx 
        
        D0$VTX_GEO:STP_xxxx.ZEB   (example file D0$STP:VTX_STPFILE.DAT)

        For D0geant data default file from D0$STP is read automatically.


    o control parameters

        D0$TRACKING_UTIL$DZERO:VERTEX.RCP
        D0$TRACKING_UTIL$VTX:VTRAKS.RCP

    o data files

        Data file may be generated by running D0GEANT using a file of ISAJET 
        events (examples: D0$ROOT:[D0GEANT.DATA]MINBIAS.GEA and 
        D0$ROOT:[D0GEANT.DATA]TTBAR.GEA). Use Geant data card SVTX to select 
        Geant output options: SVTX(1)=1. for raw data, SVTX(2)=1. for ideal
        hits. 
